@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    _Imports.razor — the project-wide Razor imports for every .razor page in
    this app.

    The Components.Web line is LOAD-BEARING (a recorded footgun, not a
    formality): bind and event tag helpers are namespace-scoped like
    components, so WITHOUT this @using in scope the compiler emits
    `@bind`/`@onclick` as LITERAL MARKUP — with ZERO diagnostics and a green
    build — silently dead on a native shell. Do not remove it because "nothing
    uses Web here".

    BlazorNative.Components is the LIBRARY namespace (the Bn* widgets your
    pages compose); BlazorNative.Core carries the contracts you inject
    (INavigationManager, IMobileBridge). Your own pages live in this project's
    namespace, which is in scope implicitly.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.Web
@using BlazorNative.Components
@using BlazorNative.Core
